## 🎮 Setup (Combined Deck)

1. Remove all **Crumbling Cookies** and **Milk Splashes** from the combined deck.
2. Deal **7 cards** to each player. Then deal **1 Milk Splash** to each player *(8 cards total per player)*.
3. Shuffle Crumbling Cookies back in — **one fewer than the number of players**:
   - 3 players → 2 · 4 players → 3 · 5 players → 4 · 6 players → 5
   - Leftover Milk Splashes? Shuffle up to **2 extras** back into the deck.
4. Shuffle the deck.
5. **Youngest player goes first.**

---

## 🎲 The Cookie Jar Roll *(4+ Players Only)*

Once per turn, **before drawing**, any player may choose to **Tempt the Jar** — but only if the discard pile contains **4 or more cards**.

Roll the die and compare your result to the **number of Milk Splashes currently in the discard pile**:

| Die Result vs. Milk Splashes in Discard | Effect |
|------------------------------------------|--------|
| **Higher** than Milk Splashes | Skip your draw phase AND discard 1 card from your hand |
| **Lower** than Milk Splashes | Draw 2 cards immediately *(replaces normal draw)* |
| **Exactly equal** to Milk Splashes | Take 1 Milk Splash from the discard pile into your hand |

> 💡 Keep Milk Splashes in a separate discard pile, slightly spread out so all players can count them at a glance.

*The jar knows what you want. It also knows how to hurt you.*

